20/04/2009
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- International ice hockey player Kiril Vuzharov was killed early on Saturday (April 18th) outside a nightclub in Sofia.
An assailant or assailants stabbed Vuzharov, who was attending a birthday party in the club, to death, as well as killing the friend whose birthday Vuzharov was celebrating.
A third friend suffered serious injuries.
Vuzharov, 21, recently joined Bulgaria's national ice hockey team.
(Reuters, BNT, BNR, bTV - 18/04/09)
